<br>
Katta Castellum is very easy to get to with Invis (Nexus, Haven, Echo, Fungal, Twilight, Katta). Sure, that's a lot of zones, but they're all sooo small. It takes more time to zone from one to the next than it does to run through them.<br>
<br>
Without invis, Fungus Grove would be &quot;ugly&quot;, so you have to go up through Tenebrous (Nexus, Haven, Paludal, Hollowshade, Grimling, Tenebrous, Katta). This is a little longer, but easily do-able. Tenebrous is a dangerous place, but many things see invisible there anyway. Actually, for this path, Levitate is a very handy spell, if you have it.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I'm not sure why youngsters would need to get to Katta Castellum anyway. The only reason I can think of is to do the House of Midst quest to raise faction in Haven, but that's not really necessary. <p>Grimwyrd Storm<BR>
